# Architecture Guidelines

## Code Architecture Principles

### Component Structure
- Keep components modular and reusable
- Follow single responsibility principle
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Implement proper error handling

### File Organization
```
src/
  components/
    resume/
      - Resume.tsx (main component)
      - ResumeSection.tsx (section wrapper)
      - SkillBar.tsx (skill display)
      - ProjectCard.tsx (project display)
      - WorkEntry.tsx (work experience)
  data/
    - resume.ts (resume data structure)
  styles/
    - components.css (component styles)
```

### Data Structure
- Centralize resume data in `src/data/resume.ts`
- Use TypeScript interfaces for type safety
- Keep data structure consistent and extensible

### Styling Approach
- Use Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling
- Maintain retro/pixel art theme consistency
- Ensure responsive design for mobile and desktop
- Use CSS custom properties for theming

### PDF Generation
- Use Puppeteer for PDF export
- Ensure ATS-friendly headings in PDF mode
- Remove interactive elements (games, toggles) from PDF
- Optimize for print/PDF rendering

### Performance Optimization
- Lazy load components where appropriate
- Optimize images and assets
- Use code splitting for better load times
- Implement proper caching strategies

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure proper ARIA labels
- Maintain keyboard navigation
- Test with screen readers

### State Management
- Use React hooks for local state
- Keep state as local as possible
- Avoid prop drilling
- Consider context for theme/global state

### Error Handling
- Implement error boundaries
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Log errors appropriately
- Handle edge cases gracefully
